Title: Urquhart (Brian) Collection of Material about Ralph Bunche, ca. 1932-1972
AltTitle.other: Collection of material about Ralph Bunche, ca. 1932-1972.|~|Brian Urquhart collection of material about Ralph Bunche
Description.abstract: Sir Brian Urquhart (b.1919) was active in the organization and direction of the United Nations (UN) Emergency Force in Middle East (1956) and responsible for the organization and direction of UN peace-keeping operations and special political assignments. Ralph Bunche (1904-1971) was the undersecretary for special political affairs at the UN (1958-67) and undersecretary general (1968). He was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize in 1950. The collection consists of papers of, about, and collected by Ralph J. Bunche and later used by Brian Urquhart to write Ralph Bunche: an American Life (1993).

Title: United Nations Under-Secretary Bunche comes to Gaza
Description.note: "UN 53656 -- Gaza, 11 March 1957 -- U.N. Under-Secretary Ralph Bunche today came to Gaza for a 24-hour visit. He is shown here stepping off his plane, after arriving by air from Abu Suweir, the base camp of the U.N. Emergency Force (UNEF) in Egypt. He was accompanied by Maj. Gen. E.L.M. Burns, Commander of UNEF. Dr. Bunche will visit some of the units in the Gaza area he will also confer with staff officers of the Force and officials of the U.N. Relief & Works Agency for Palestine Refugees (UNRWA)."|~|Digitization took place as part of the California Cultures Project.

Description.note: Digitization took place as part of the California Cultures Project.|~|Ralph Bunche, U.N. Under-Secretary for Special Political Affairs, visited Nicosia, Cyprus in the course of routine visits to Gaza and Kashmir to study the problems and needs of the United Nations truce supervision and peace force operations in these areas. In this photograph, Bunche meets Turkish Cypriots in the refugee camp at Hamitkoy, near Nicosia.
